Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
First, you need to look at the traffic signal across the street in order to know if you can cross the street or not. Second, when you make sure you can pass, you can to look on your left side first and then the right side to make sure all the cars have stopped. Third, if all the situation is good, you can now cross the street quickly.